subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
Figs. 15–18
) with basal bulb and parameres comparatively large (
Figs. 15, 18
). Median lobe of aedeagus strongly asymmetrical, sinuously curved, in lateral view (
Fig. 16
) arcuate, with ventral margin slightly convex in middle portion; almost transverse apical capitulum slightly hooked dorsally; in dorsal view apical portion (
Fig. 17
) sharply bent to the right; terminal lamella narrow, much longer than wide. Apical orifice vast and strongly curved along median lobe. Internal sac without sclerotic elements.
